Parliament, Wednesday, 17 March 2021 – The Ad Hoc Committee on Section 100 Intervention in the North West Province will tomorrow interact with various stakeholders to get their views on the progress and impact of the intervention in the province. The committee has been in the province to review its progress and impact in stabilising the provincial administration and ensuring effective service delivery.
	
	Some of the stakeholders engaged will include traditional leaders and faith and community organisations. The meeting is intended to understand the various stakeholders’ experiences of the intervention.
	
	The committee will also interact with the Inter-Ministerial Task Team (IMTT) to get an update on the intervention. The meeting with the IMTT was deferred to tomorrow following a request from the intervention team.
	
	Details of the meetings
	Date: Thursday, 18 March 2021
	Time: 10:00
	Venue: Madiba Banquet Hall, Potchefstroom
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE AD HOC COMMITTEE ON SECTION 100 INTERVENTION IN THE NORTH WEST PROVINCE, MR CHINA DODOVU.
	
	For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer:
